Menu="OtherSettings"
Title="HPE Management"
Icon="server"
Tag="icon-hpe-mgmt"
---
<?PHP
/* HPE Management — unRAID settings page.
 * Config persists at /boot/config/plugins/hpe-mgmt/hpe-mgmt.cfg.
 * Save handler lives in include/settings.php.
 */

$plugin   = "hpe-mgmt";
$plugdir  = "/usr/local/emhttp/plugins/$plugin";
$cfg_path = "/boot/config/plugins/$plugin/$plugin.cfg";
require_once "$plugdir/include/cfg.php";
$defaults = hpe_mgmt_read_cfg("$plugdir/$plugin.cfg.default");
$current  = file_exists($cfg_path) ? hpe_mgmt_read_cfg($cfg_path) : $defaults;

$stack        = $current['STACK']           ?? 'modern';
$extras       = $current['EXTRAS']          ?? '';
$mcp_dist     = $current['MCP_DIST']        ?? 'CentOS';
$mcp_ver      = $current['MCP_VER']         ?? '8';
$spp_ver      = $current['SPP_LEGACY_VER']  ?? '2022.03.0';
$install_amsd = $current['INSTALL_AMSD']    ?? '0';
$snmp_rev     = $current['ENABLE_SNMP_REV'] ?? '0';
$gpg          = $current['VERIFY_GPG']      ?? '1';

$extras_set = array_flip(preg_split('/\s+/', trim($extras)));

function chk($cond) { return $cond ? 'checked'  : ''; }
function sel($cond) { return $cond ? 'selected' : ''; }

/* Service status via rc script — best effort.  Missing script means the
 * plugin has never been applied yet. */
$rc = "/etc/rc.d/rc.$plugin";
$status = is_executable($rc)
    ? trim(shell_exec("$rc status 2>&1"))
    : "(not yet applied — click Apply below)";

/* If legacy/both and hpsmhd is listening, expose a link to its web UI. */
$smh_link = '';
if (in_array($stack, ['legacy','both'], true)) {
    $listen = trim(shell_exec(
        "ss -tln 2>/dev/null | awk '\$4 ~ /:2381\$/ {print \$4; exit}'"
    ));
    if ($listen !== '') {
        $host = $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME'] ?? 'your-unraid';
        $smh_link = "https://{$host}:2381/";
    }
}
?>

<form markdown="1" name="hpe_mgmt_form" method="POST"
      action="/plugins/hpe-mgmt/include/settings.php" target="progressFrame">

Stack to install and run:
: <input type="radio" name="STACK" value="modern" <?=chk($stack==='modern')?>> Modern (ssacli + hponcfg) — recommended
  <input type="radio" name="STACK" value="legacy" <?=chk($stack==='legacy')?>> Legacy SMH (hpsmh + CMA + :2381 web UI)
  <input type="radio" name="STACK" value="both"   <?=chk($stack==='both')?>>   Both

Install amsd daemon family (Tier 2 Modern):
: <input type="checkbox" name="INSTALL_AMSD" value="1" <?=chk($install_amsd==='1')?>>
  Adds amsd and the cpq* storage/nic/ide agents.  Pulls in the bundled
  EL8 compat libs automatically.

Extra packages:
: <input type="checkbox" name="EX_ssaducli" <?=chk(isset($extras_set['ssaducli']))?>> ssaducli (Smart Storage diagnostics)
  <input type="checkbox" name="EX_storcli"  <?=chk(isset($extras_set['storcli']))?>>  storcli (LSI/Broadcom RAID)
  <input type="checkbox" name="EX_hponcfg"  <?=chk(isset($extras_set['hponcfg']))?>>  hponcfg (iLO config from OS)

SNMP bridge daemons (`*_rev`):
: <input type="checkbox" name="ENABLE_SNMP_REV" value="1" <?=chk($snmp_rev==='1')?>>
  Only useful if you run snmpd on the host.  Off by default.

HPE SDR (Modern source):
: distribution
  <select name="MCP_DIST">
    <?php foreach (['CentOS','Alma','OracleLinux'] as $d): ?>
      <option <?=sel($d === $mcp_dist)?>><?=$d?></option>
    <?php endforeach; ?>
  </select>
  version
  <select name="MCP_VER">
    <?php foreach (['7','8','9','current'] as $v): ?>
      <option <?=sel($v === $mcp_ver)?>><?=$v?></option>
    <?php endforeach; ?>
  </select>

HPE SPP (Legacy SMH source):
: version
  <select name="SPP_LEGACY_VER">
    <?php foreach (['2019.03.0','2020.03.0','2021.05.0','2022.03.0'] as $v): ?>
      <option <?=sel($v === $spp_ver)?>><?=$v?></option>
    <?php endforeach; ?>
  </select>
  (2022.03.0 is the last SPP that shipped hpsmh; 2022.08+ dropped it.)

Verify GPG signatures + per-RPM hash:
: <input type="checkbox" name="VERIFY_GPG" value="1" <?=chk($gpg==='1')?>>
  (strongly recommended — off makes the plugin trust HTTPS alone)

&nbsp;
: <input type="submit" name="apply"   value="Apply (install/reinstall)">
  <input type="submit" name="restart" value="Restart services">
  <input type="submit" name="stop"    value="Stop services">

Service status:
: <pre style="font-family:monospace; white-space:pre-wrap;"><?=htmlspecialchars($status)?></pre>

<?php if ($smh_link): ?>
SMH web UI is up:
: <a href="<?=htmlspecialchars($smh_link)?>" target="_blank"><?=htmlspecialchars($smh_link)?></a>
  (log in with the root OS account — SMH authenticates against PAM.)
<?php endif; ?>
</form>

<iframe name="progressFrame"
        style="width:100%; height:30em; border:1px solid #555; margin-top:1em;
               background:#111; color:#eee; font-family:monospace; font-size:0.9em;">
</iframe>
